    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-07T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-07T23:00:00-05:00" n="465"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3461: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1" type="from">Adams</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-08T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 8, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Communists are heavily attacking Hwangpei city 20 miles north of Hankow.
                    Although Shekow, 10 miles north of Hankow, is protected by strong military
                    trenches, I have, as a precautionary measure, advised the American women and
                    children of the Lutheran Theological Seminary there to withdraw therefrom for a
                    few days. Legation and Nanking informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Adams</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
